            . The last witness brought the prisoner to me and gave charge of him; the lead was taken from a building contiguous to the Hospital of Bethlem. The prisoner said before the Alderman that poverty drove him to do what he had done.</p>
               <p>The prisoner in his defence denied the charge, but called no witnesses.</p>
